rst half of the twentieth century. Employing the greatest scenic artists, Léon Bakst and Alexander Benois; the distinguished composers Igor Stravinsky, Arthur Honegger, and Claude Debussy; celebrated writers including Paul Valéry and André Gide; and the brilliant choreographer Bronislava Nijinska, Rubinstein transformed twentieth-century theater and dance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChoreographerszFrancezParisvBiography. 0aWomen dancerszFrancezParisvBiography. 0aWomen dancerszRussia (Federation)vBiography. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Performing Arts. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848799140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438487991423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438487991/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles